    SELECT ID 
    FROM t1
    INNER JOIN t2 ON t1.Notes LIKE &#39;%&#39; + t2.Code + &#39;%&#39;

If different `Code`s might appear in the same `Note`, using an `EXISTS` condition with a correlated subquery is also an option, as it would avoid duplicating records in the output:

    SELECT ID
    FROM t1
    WHERE EXISTS (
        SELECT 1 FROM t2 WHERE t1.Notes LIKE &#39;%&#39; + t2.Code + &#39;%&#39;
    )

