The **redirect** statement in codeigniter sends the user to the specified web page using a redirect header statement.
    
Load URL helper in controller or model or you can load in `config/autoload.php` for global access, which is loaded in the following way:

    
In controller or Model like this:
&gt; [$this-&gt;load-&gt;helper(&#39;url&#39;)][1];

If you do not want to load in controller or model then load in `config/autoload.php`:

&gt; $autoload[&#39;helper&#39;] = array(&#39;url&#39;);

  [1]: https://codeigniter.com/user_guide/general/helpers.html

And call redirect function like this:

&gt; redirect(&#39;/auth/login&#39;, &#39;refresh&#39;);

If your Auth controller path is  Controller/Admin/Auth
then use

    redirect(&#39;admin/auth/login&#39;, &#39;refresh&#39;);

If it is Controller/Auth then use 

    redirect(&#39;auth/login&#39;, &#39;refresh&#39;);

You need to load url helper in both case. i suggest you to autoload url helper in codeigniter project.

